message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a method based on a pre-trained convolutional neural network to assess the healing progress of the Achilles tendon. This involves training the network on MRI images and using linear regression on the PCA-reduced space of the features to assess treatment progress. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Medical Imaging (cs.MED), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NEURON) sub-categories.
